title.narrative: Procurement of Services for Bihar Nutrition and Health Programme

description.narrative: This activity (Procurement of Services for Bihar Nutrition and Health Programme) is a component of Sector Wide Approach to Strengthening Health (SWASTH) in Bihar reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £34,725,493. This component benefits India, and works in the following sector(s): Health policy and administrative management, Basic health care, Basic nutrition, Reproductive health care, Basic drinking water supply and basic sanitation. , with the following implementing partners: CARE International UK, Population Council, PwC India. The start date is 01-04-2008 and the end date is 31-03-2016.
